<BaseLayout title="Bornga Beauty World: The KBBQ Spot Worth the MRT Ride" description="Bornga Beauty World review — a Korean BBQ restaurant in Beauty World, Singapore. Full review with ratings, prices, and what to order.">

  <header class="article-header">
    <div class="article-pillar-tag"><a href="/eat/">Eat</a> &middot; Review</div>
    <h1>Bornga Beauty World: The KBBQ Spot Worth the MRT Ride</h1>
    <div class="article-byline">
      <span class="author">Eric Sim</span>
      <span class="separator">/</span>
      <time datetime="2026-03-18">March 18, 2026</time>
      <span class="separator">/</span>
      <span>8 min read</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <figure class="article-featured-image">
    <div class="image-placeholder">[ featured: Bornga Beauty World exterior at night ]</div>
    <figcaption>Bornga's Beauty World outlet occupies a generous corner lot on Cheong Chin Nam Road. Photo: Eric Sim / The Hansang</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="article-video">
    <div class="article-video-inner">
      <div class="article-video-placeholder">
        <div class="article-video-play"></div>
        <span>Watch on Instagram</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="article-video-caption">Watch the full review on Instagram <a href="https://www.instagram.com/thehansang.sg">@thehansang.sg</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="article-layout">
    <article class="article-content">

      <aside class="quick-take" aria-label="Quick summary">
        <div class="quick-take-title">Quick Take</div>
        <div class="quick-take-grid">
          <div class="quick-take-item"><span class="quick-take-label">Rating</span><span class="quick-take-value rating">7.5 / 10</span></div>
          <div class="quick-take-item"><span class="quick-take-label">Price Range</span><span class="quick-take-value">$$&ndash;$$$</span></div>
          <div class="quick-take-item"><span class="quick-take-label">Best Dish</span><span class="quick-take-value">Woo Samgyup (beef brisket)</span></div>
          <div class="quick-take-item"><span class="quick-take-label">Skip This</span><span class="quick-take-value">Seafood Pancake</span></div>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <p>Let me be upfront: getting to Beauty World for Korean BBQ requires commitment. You are taking the Downtown Line to a station that most Singaporeans associate with tuition centres and army surplus shops. But Bornga, the Seoul-born chain that opened its second Singapore outlet here in late 2025, makes a surprisingly strong case for the trek.</p>

      <p>The original Bornga in Tanjong Pagar has been a solid option for years, but it always felt like it was coasting on its location. The Beauty World branch feels different. The space is bigger, the ventilation is noticeably better, and the kitchen seems sharper.</p>

      <h2>The Space</h2>

      <p>Bornga Beauty World occupies a corner lot along Cheong Chin Nam Road, just a three-minute walk from Beauty World MRT. The interior leans into the industrial-Korean aesthetic that every KBBQ spot seems contractually obligated to adopt: exposed brick, dark metal fixtures, wooden tabletops. It works. The dining room seats around 80, and every table has its own built-in grill and overhead exhaust.</p>

      <figure class="inline-photo">
        <div class="image-placeholder">[ photo: interior dining room with tabletop grills ]</div>
        <figcaption>The Beauty World branch is noticeably more spacious than the Tanjong Pagar original.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2>The Meat</h2>

      <p>This is where Bornga earns its keep. The <strong class="dish-name">Woo Samgyup</strong> <span class="dish-price">(S$32)</span>, a thick-cut beef brisket, is the star of the menu and the reason to come here. The marbling is generous without being excessive, and the meat has real beef flavour.</p>

      <p>The <strong class="dish-name">Kkotsal</strong> <span class="dish-price">(S$28)</span>, boneless short rib, is equally impressive. Thin slices with excellent marbling that caramelise beautifully on the grill.</p>

      <figure class="inline-photo">
        <div class="image-placeholder">[ photo: woo samgyup on the grill, showing marbling ]</div>
        <figcaption>Woo Samgyup (S$32) on the charcoal grill. The marbling on these cuts has been consistently good across two visits.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <aside class="ad-inline" aria-label="Advertisement"><div class="ad-slot"><span class="ad-slot-label">Partner</span>Advertisement</div></aside>

      <h2>The Banchan</h2>

      <p>Bornga's banchan spread is above average for Singapore. You get the standard six to eight dishes: kimchi, pickled radish, bean sprouts, spinach, japchae, and a rotating seasonal option.</p>

      <h2>What to Skip</h2>

      <p>The <strong class="dish-name">Haemul Pajeon</strong> <span class="dish-price">(S$22)</span>, the seafood pancake, was a letdown on both visits. The batter was too thick and not crispy enough at the edges.</p>

      <h2>Service and Value</h2>

      <p>Service was efficient on both visits. For two people, expect to spend S$70 to S$100 depending on how much meat you order. That puts Bornga in the mid-range for KBBQ in Singapore.</p>

      <aside class="ad-inline" aria-label="Advertisement"><div class="ad-slot"><span class="ad-slot-label">Partner</span>Advertisement</div></aside>

      <aside class="info-block" aria-label="Restaurant information">
        <div class="info-block-title">Restaurant Info</div>
        <dl>
          <dt>Address</dt><dd>6 Cheong Chin Nam Road, #01-11, Singapore 599738</dd>
          <dt>MRT</dt><dd>Beauty World (DT5), 3-min walk</dd>
          <dt>Hours</dt><dd>Mon&ndash;Thu 11:30am&ndash;3pm, 5&ndash;10pm<br>Fri&ndash;Sun 11:30am&ndash;10:30pm</dd>
          <dt>Price Range</dt><dd>S$35&ndash;$50 per person</dd>
          <dt>Reservation</dt><dd>Walk-in only. No reservations.</dd>
          <dt>Halal</dt><dd>No</dd>
        </dl>
      </aside>

      <section class="verdict" aria-label="Verdict">
        <h2>Verdict</h2>
        <div class="verdict-rating">7.5 <span>/ 10</span></div>
        <p class="verdict-summary">Bornga Beauty World is the strongest new KBBQ opening in Singapore in the past year. The beef cuts are excellent, the ventilation actually works, and the banchan spread is above average. The seafood pancake is a miss, but the overall experience is worth the MRT ride to Beauty World.</p>
      </section>

    </article>

